of started becoming the
language spoken by this community

00:32:42.460 --> 00:32:46.800
as they had children and adapted
to life in the United States.

00:32:46.800 --> 00:32:52.600
Chapter devoted to, as I said
before, leisure, fun, courtship,

00:32:52.600 --> 00:32:54.490
marriage, things like that.

00:32:54.490 --> 00:32:57.490
Again, beautiful photographs.

00:32:57.490 --> 00:32:59.610
The beach, this is
Rye Beach, New York,

00:32:59.610 --> 00:33:02.050
bunch of Asturian girls [laughter].

00:33:04.380 --> 00:33:10.600
It was very common to take
these kind of gag photographs,

00:33:10.600 --> 00:33:14.130
especially a newly arrived
Spanish immigrant would think,

00:33:14.130 --> 00:33:16.840
oh what a joke, I'm driving a car.

00:33:16.840 --> 00:33:19.930
It was like it was so outlandish,
especially if they sent this back

00:33:19.930 --> 00:33:22.770
to the village, that it was funny.

00:33:22.770 --> 00:33:25.680
But the remarkable thing
is that 3 or 5 years later,

00:33:25.680 --> 00:33:29.110
they'll be sending back photos
of them actually driving cars.

00:33:29.110 --> 00:33:33.480
But, yeah, right now it's a gag.

00:33:33.480 --> 00:33:36.160
Many beautiful studio
portraits often taken

00:33:36.160 --> 00:33:38.830
to send back to the relatives.

00:33:38.830 --> 00:33:42.930
This is a pool room in Ybor
City, not a place you'd want

00:33:42.930 --> 00:33:47.940
to get caught late at night,
if you're not from Ybor City.

00:33:47.940 --> 00:33:52.340
This is a gorgeous photograph,
it looks like Asturias.

00:33:52.340 --> 00:33:58.490
The Asturian born Angel Alonso
[phonetic] who lost his job

00:33:58.490 --> 00:34:00.560
in New York during the Depression,

00:34:00.560 --> 00:34:03.720
and went back to doing what he knew
how to do best which was farming.

00:34:03.720 --> 00:34:07.880
He moved to upstate New York and
rented a farm and grew apples

00:34:07.880 --> 00:34:13.830
and made hay and had cows and
he's in Walk Hill, New York,

00:34:13.830 --> 00:34:16.950
and it looks like he's
back in Navares Asturias

00:34:16.950 --> 00:34:20.440
which was his hometown
near Arriondas.

00:34:20.440 --> 00:34:24.060
His children were born in New
York and Manuel is still alive,

00:34:24.060 --> 00:34:27.490
one of my main informants,
the fellow on the right.

00:34:27.490 --> 00:34:33.420
He's 95. That farm that they
set up became, eventually,

00:34:33.420 --> 00:34:35.650
a kind of boarding house, a
hotel, where they would take

00:34:35.650 --> 00:34:38.010
in other Spanish families in the
summer months who were trying

00:34:38.010 --> 00:34:39.410
to get away from the
heat of the city

00:34:39.410 --> 00:34:43.500
